summary: This research investigates how eye movement miscue analysis can enhance readers' understanding of their reading processes and identities. It focuses on two college readers who, despite their success, have doubts about their reading abilities. By analyzing their reading behavior and encouraging reflection on their assumptions about reading, the study aims to address misconceptions and empower readers as active participants in the meaning-making process. The findings also provide practical strategies for educators to help students overcome common reading misunderstandings.
